.TH "__dma_request_channel" 9 "__dma_request_channel" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__dma_request_channel \- try to allocate an exclusive channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct dma_chan *" __dma_request_channel
.BI "(const dma_cap_mask_t *mask "  ","
.BI "dma_filter_fn fn "  ","
.BI "void *fn_param "  ","
.BI "struct device_node *np "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mask" 12
capabilities that the channel must satisfy
.IP "fn" 12
optional callback to disposition available channels
.IP "fn_param" 12
opaque parameter to pass to \fBdma_filter_fn\fP
.IP "np" 12
device node to look for DMA channels
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns pointer to appropriate DMA channel on success or NULL.
